26/06/2006
ATHENS, Greece -- Defence Minister Evangelos Meimarakis announced planned changes in military service, aimed at upgrading the country's defence capacities. In an interview published in Sunday's (25 June) edition of Adesmeftos Typos, he said the ministry is considering the introduction of mandatory recruitment at the age of 19, and reducing the term of military service in border regions from 18 months to five months. The ministry is also mulling over adjustments to the current promotion system for army officers and non-commissioned officers. (Eleftheria - 26/06/06; Adesmeftos Typos, ERT - 25/06/06) 
